('TXT HYBE Second Group Fact', 'TXT (Tomorrow X Together) debuted on March 4, 2019 as HYBE''s (then Big Hit) second boy group after BTS. Their debut album "The Dream Chapter: STAR" broke first-week sales records for the label. #TXT', 'K-pop Facts', 'fact_card', NULL, 'TXT', 'txt', 'TXT debuted March 4, 2019 as HYBE''s second boy group', 'Following in BTS''s footsteps from day one', 'March 4, 2019', false, 'draft', ARRAY['#kpop', '#TXT', '#MOA', '#HYBE', '#kpopfact'], 'fact_card', 82),
('LE SSERAFIM Name Meaning', 'LE SSERAFIM''s name is an anagram of "I''M FEARLESS". The group debuted May 2, 2022 under HYBE Labels and Source Music, with their debut song "FEARLESS" topping Korean charts. #LESSERAFIM', 'K-pop Facts', 'fact_card', NULL, 'LE SSERAFIM', 'le-sserafim', 'LE SSERAFIM is an anagram of "I''M FEARLESS"', 'A hidden message right in their name', 'May 2022', false, 'draft', ARRAY['#kpop', '#LESSERAFIM', '#FEARNOT', '#kpopfact', '#kpoptrivia'], 'fact_card', 83),
('NCT Unlimited Members Concept', 'NCT operates on an "unlimited members" concept with no set group size. The concept is divided into sub-units: NCT U, NCT 127, NCT DREAM, and WayV. Over 20 members have been added since debut. #NCT', 'K-pop Facts', 'fact_card', NULL, 'NCT', 'nct', 'NCT has no fixed member count - they are "unlimited"', 'NCT U, 127, DREAM, WayV are all sub-units', NULL, false, 'draft', ARRAY['#kpop', '#NCT', '#NCTzen', '#kpopfact', '#kpoptrivia'], 'fact_card', 84),
('ITZY JYP Debut Record', 'ITZY debuted on February 12, 2019 with "Dalla Dalla", which set records for the most-viewed JYP girl group debut MV in 24 hours at the time. The song reached #1 on Korean music charts. #ITZY', 'K-pop Facts', 'fact_card', NULL, 'ITZY', 'itzy', 'ITZY''s "Dalla Dalla" broke JYP girl group debut records', 'Reaching #1 in Korea on day one', 'February 12, 2019', false, 'draft', ARRAY['#kpop', '#ITZY', '#MIDZY', '#kpopfact', '#kpoptrivia'], 'fact_card', 85),
-- General K-pop facts (sort 86-110)
('PSY Gangnam Style 1 Billion Views', '"Gangnam Style" by PSY was the first YouTube video to reach 1 billion views in December 2012, opening the world''s eyes to K-pop. It was also the most-liked video at the time. #PSY #kpop', 'K-pop Facts', 'fact_card', NULL, NULL, NULL, '"Gangnam Style" was the first YouTube video to hit 1 billion views', 'PSY opened the world''s eyes to K-pop in 2012', 'December 2012', false, 'draft', ARRAY['#kpop', '#PSY', '#GangnamStyle', '#kpopfact', '#kpophistory'], 'fact_card', 86),
('K-pop Global Revenue Fact', 'The K-pop industry generates over $10 billion in global annual revenue, including music, merchandise, concerts, and media. South Korea''s cultural exports have transformed the global music market. #kpop', 'K-pop Facts', 'fact_card', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'K-pop generates over $10 billion annually worldwide', 'South Korea''s cultural impact is now a global force', NULL, false, 'draft', ARRAY['#kpop', '#kpopfact', '#kpopindustry', '#hallyu', '#kpopbusiness'], 'fact_card', 87),
('SM Entertainment Founded 1995', 'SM Entertainment was founded by producer Lee Soo Man in 1995 and is one of the "Big 4" K-pop agencies. SM launched H.O.T., BoA, TVXQ, Super Junior, Girls'' Generation, EXO, and aespa. #kpop', 'K-pop Facts', 'fact_card', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'SM Entertainment was founded in 1995', 'The agency that launched H.O.T., TVXQ, EXO, aespa and more', '1995', false, 'draft', ARRAY['#kpop', '#SMEntertainment', '#kpopfact', '#kpophistory', '#hallyu'], 'fact_card', 88),
('BTS Boy With Luv YouTube Record', '"Boy With Luv" feat. Halsey by BTS set a YouTube 24-hour viewing record in 2019 with 74.6 million views. The collaboration between BTS and Halsey helped bridge K-pop and Western pop. #BTS', 'K-pop Facts', 'fact_card', NULL, 'BTS', 'bts', '"Boy With Luv" set a 24-hour YouTube record in 2019', 'With 74.6 million views in a single day', 'April 2019', false, 'draft', ARRAY['#kpop', '#BTS', '#BoyWithLuv', '#Halsey', '#kpopfact'], 'fact_card', 89),
('Stray Kids Felix From Australia', 'Stray Kids'' Felix is from Sydney, Australia (like Bang Chan). Felix is known for his distinctive deep voice, which creates a striking contrast with the group''s softer vocal elements. #StrayKids', 'K-pop Facts', 'fact_card', NULL, 'Stray Kids', 'stray-kids', 'Stray Kids'' Felix is also from Sydney, Australia', 'Two Australians in the same K-pop group is rare!', NULL, false, 'draft', ARRAY['#kpop', '#StrayKids', '#Felix', '#STAY', '#kpopfact'], 'fact_card', 90),
('IVE After Like Sample Fact', 'IVE''s "After Like" (2022) samples Diana Ross''s 1980 classic "I''m Coming Out". The song became a massive hit and introduced many young fans to the original Diana Ross track. #IVE #kpopfact', 'K-pop Facts', 'fact_card', NULL, 'IVE', 'ive', '"After Like" by IVE samples Diana Ross''s "I''m Coming Out"', 'Introducing a classic to a new generation', '2022', false, 'draft', ARRAY['#kpop', '#IVE', '#AfterLike', '#DianaRoss', '#kpopfact'], 'fact_card', 91),
('BLACKPINK Most Instagram Followers', 'BLACKPINK is the most-followed music group on Instagram, with over 75 million followers on the group account. Lisa individually has over 100 million Instagram followers, a K-pop record. #BLACKPINK', 'K-pop Facts', 'fact_card', NULL, 'BLACKPINK', 'blackpink', 'BLACKPINK is the most-followed music group on Instagram', 'Lisa individually has 100M+ followers - a K-pop record', NULL, false, 'draft', ARRAY['#kpop', '#BLACKPINK', '#BLINK', '#kpopfact', '#kpoprecord'], 'fact_card', 92),
('Dreamcatcher Rock Concept Fact', 'Dreamcatcher debuted January 13, 2017 and is unique in K-pop for their consistent dark rock/metal-influenced concept. Their concept is based on nightmares and dreams throughout their discography. #DC', 'K-pop Facts', 'fact_card', NULL, 'Dreamcatcher', 'dreamcatcher', 'Dreamcatcher''s entire concept is based on nightmares', 'The only K-pop group with a full dark rock concept', 'January 2017', false, 'draft', ARRAY['#kpop', '#Dreamcatcher', '#InSomnia', '#kpopfact', '#kpoprock'], 'fact_card', 93),
('MONSTA X First K-pop at AMAs', 'MONSTA X was the first K-pop group to perform at the American Music Awards (AMAs) in 2019, performing "Who Do U Love?" with France Joli. A major milestone for K-pop in the US. #MONSTAX', 'K-pop Facts', 'fact_card', NULL, 'MONSTA X', 'monsta-x', 'MONSTA X were the first K-pop group to perform at the AMAs', 'Making history at the American Music Awards in 2019', 'November 2019', false, 'draft', ARRAY['#kpop', '#MONSTAX', '#Monbebe', '#AMAs', '#kpopfact'], 'fact_card', 94),
('BTOB Debut 2012 Fact', 'BTOB (Born to Beat) debuted on March 21, 2012 under Cube Entertainment. They are known for their emotional ballads and powerful vocals, often cited as one of the best vocal groups in K-pop. #BTOB', 'K-pop Facts', 'fact_card', NULL, 'BTOB', 'btob', 'BTOB debuted March 21, 2012', 'Known as one of K-pop''s best vocal groups', 'March 21, 2012', false, 'draft', ARRAY['#kpop', '#BTOB', '#Melody', '#kpopfact', '#kpoptrivia'], 'fact_card', 95),
('STAYC Teen Fresh Concept', 'STAYC debuted November 12, 2020 under High Up Entertainment, which was founded by members of B2ST/BEAST. Their "teen fresh" concept has made them one of the most charming 4th gen groups. #STAYC', 'K-pop Facts', 'fact_card', NULL, 'STAYC', 'stayc', 'STAYC was founded by ex-B2ST members'' entertainment company', 'Their "teen fresh" concept defined 4th gen girl group charm', 'November 2020', false, 'draft', ARRAY['#kpop', '#STAYC', '#SWITH', '#kpopfact', '#kpoptrivia'], 'fact_card', 96),
('GOT7 Jackson Wang Global Fact', 'GOT7''s Jackson Wang (from Hong Kong) became one of K-pop''s most globally successful solo artists, achieving hit records in China, the US, and Europe independently after leaving JYP. #GOT7 #Jackson', 'K-pop Facts', 'fact_card', NULL, 'GOT7', 'got7', 'GOT7''s Jackson Wang is one of K-pop''s most global solo artists', 'Charting in China, the US, and Europe simultaneously', NULL, false, 'draft', ARRAY['#kpop', '#GOT7', '#JacksonWang', '#IGOT7', '#kpopfact'], 'fact_card', 97),
('TREASURE YG Debut Fact', 'TREASURE debuted on August 7, 2020 under YG Entertainment with a 12-member lineup selected from the "YG Treasure Box" survival show. They released 2 albums simultaneously on debut day. #TREASURE', 'K-pop Facts', 'fact_card', NULL, 'TREASURE', 'treasure', 'TREASURE debuted with 12 members on August 7, 2020', 'Selected through YG''s "Treasure Box" survival show', 'August 7, 2020', false, 'draft', ARRAY['#kpop', '#TREASURE', '#Teume', '#kpopfact', '#kpoptrivia'], 'fact_card', 98),
('Kep1er Girls Planet 999 Fact', 'Kep1er was formed through the Mnet survival show "Girls Planet 999" in 2021, featuring contestants from Korea, China, and Japan. They debuted on January 3, 2022. #Kep1er #kpopfact', 'K-pop Facts', 'fact_card', NULL, 'Kep1er', 'kep1er', 'Kep1er was formed through "Girls Planet 999" in 2021', 'With members from Korea, China, and Japan', 'January 2022', false, 'draft', ARRAY['#kpop', '#Kep1er', '#Kep1ian', '#kpopfact', '#kpoptrivia'], 'fact_card', 99),
('NMIXX Mixx Pop Concept', 'NMIXX debuted February 22, 2022 under JYP with "O.O", pioneering the "mixx pop" concept - songs that blend multiple genres and tempos mid-track. The bold approach divided and fascinated fans. #NMIXX', 'K-pop Facts', 'fact_card', NULL, 'NMIXX', 'nmixx', 'NMIXX invented "mixx pop" - K-pop''s most experimental concept', 'Songs that switch genres completely mid-track', 'February 2022', false, 'draft', ARRAY['#kpop', '#NMIXX', '#NSWer', '#mixxpop', '#kpopfact'], 'fact_card', 100),
('ASTRO Cha Eunwoo Actor Fact', 'ASTRO member Cha Eunwoo became one of K-pop''s most successful actor-idols, starring in multiple hit K-dramas including "True Beauty" and "My ID is Gangnam Beauty". #ASTRO #ChaEunwoo', 'K-pop Facts', 'fact_card', NULL, 'ASTRO', 'astro', 'Cha Eunwoo of ASTRO is one of K-pop''s top actor-idols', 'Starring in hit K-dramas like "True Beauty"', NULL, false, 'draft', ARRAY['#kpop', '#ASTRO', '#ChaEunwoo', '#kpopfact', '#kdrama'], 'fact_card', 101),
('SEVENTEEN Woozi Composition Fact', 'SEVENTEEN''s Woozi (Lee Ji-hoon) is the main composer and producer of the group, having written and produced dozens of their songs. He is one of K-pop''s most prolific idol-producers. #SEVENTEEN', 'K-pop Facts', 'fact_card', NULL, 'SEVENTEEN', 'seventeen', 'SEVENTEEN''s Woozi has written dozens of their hit songs', 'One of K-pop''s most prolific idol-producers', NULL, false, 'draft', ARRAY['#kpop', '#SEVENTEEN', '#Woozi', '#CARAT', '#kpopfact'], 'fact_card', 102),
('NCT Dream Graduate Concept', 'NCT DREAM originally operated on a "graduation system" where members would leave the unit when they turned 20. This rule was later changed, allowing members like Mark to remain permanently. #NCT', 'K-pop Facts', 'fact_card', NULL, 'NCT', 'nct', 'NCT DREAM originally made members "graduate" at age 20', 'The unique rule was later changed for all members', NULL, false, 'draft', ARRAY['#kpop', '#NCT', '#NCTDream', '#NCTzen', '#kpopfact'], 'fact_card', 103),
('LE SSERAFIM IZ*ONE Alumni', 'LE SSERAFIM''s Kim Chaewon and Sakura Miyawaki were both members of project group IZ*ONE (2018-2021) before joining LE SSERAFIM. Their experience gave them a head start at debut. #LESSERAFIM', 'K-pop Facts', 'fact_card', NULL, 'LE SSERAFIM', 'le-sserafim', 'Two LE SSERAFIM members are IZ*ONE alumni', 'Chaewon and Sakura both came from the project group', NULL, false, 'draft', ARRAY['#kpop', '#LESSERAFIM', '#FEARNOT', '#IZONE', '#kpopfact'], 'fact_card', 104),
('K-pop 4th Generation Fact', 'The "4th generation" of K-pop (roughly 2018-2022) is characterized by self-producing groups, darker aesthetics, complex choreography, and a more direct connection with global fanbases. #kpop', 'K-pop Facts', 'fact_card', NULL, NULL, NULL, '4th gen K-pop: self-producing, global, and bolder than ever', 'Groups like ATEEZ, Stray Kids, aespa led this era', '2018-2022', false, 'draft', ARRAY['#kpop', '#kpopfact', '#4thgen', '#kpophistory', '#kpoptrivia'], 'fact_card', 105),
('ENHYPEN Given-Taken Debut Chart', 'ENHYPEN''s debut single "Given-Taken" (2020) charted at #8 on the Billboard World Digital Song Sales chart within its first week - one of the strongest debut performances by a 4th gen boy group. #ENHYPEN', 'K-pop Facts', 'fact_card', NULL, 'ENHYPEN', 'enhypen', 'ENHYPEN''s debut "Given-Taken" hit top 10 on Billboard', 'One of the strongest debut chart performances of 4th gen', 'November 2020', false, 'draft', ARRAY['#kpop', '#ENHYPEN', '#ENGENE', '#kpopfact', '#kpoprecord'], 'fact_card', 106),
('MAMAMOO Wheein Artist Fact', 'MAMAMOO''s Wheein is a trained visual artist who graduated from an arts high school. She incorporates her artistic skills into MV concepts and has released her own art exhibitions. #MAMAMOO #Wheein', 'K-pop Facts', 'fact_card', NULL, 'MAMAMOO', 'mamamoo', 'MAMAMOO''s Wheein is a trained visual artist', 'She graduated from an arts high school in Korea', NULL, false, 'draft', ARRAY['#kpop', '#MAMAMOO', '#Wheein', '#Moomoo', '#kpopfact'], 'fact_card', 107),
('ITZY Coachella JYP Fact', 'ITZY became the first JYP Entertainment girl group to perform at Coachella in 2023, following BLACKPINK''s headlining set. MIDZY around the world tuned in to their desert stage performance. #ITZY', 'K-pop Facts', 'fact_card', NULL, 'ITZY', 'itzy', 'ITZY were the first JYP girl group at Coachella in 2023', 'Making history alongside BLACKPINK''s headlining year', 'April 2023', false, 'draft', ARRAY['#kpop', '#ITZY', '#MIDZY', '#Coachella', '#kpopfact'], 'fact_card', 108),
('ATEEZ KQ Fellaz Origin', 'Before debuting as ATEEZ, the members were part of a pre-debut group called "KQ Fellaz". They traveled to Los Angeles to train and released pre-debut content before their 2018 debut. #ATEEZ', 'K-pop Facts', 'fact_card', NULL, 'ATEEZ', 'ateez', 'ATEEZ were originally called "KQ Fellaz" before debut', 'They trained in LA and built buzz before debuting in 2018', '2018', false, 'draft', ARRAY['#kpop', '#ATEEZ', '#ATINY', '#kpopfact', '#kpophistory'], 'fact_card', 109),
('aespa SM Universe Lore', 'aespa exists within the "SM Culture Universe" (SMCU) - a shared lore connecting SM Entertainment artists. Their concept of the real world and virtual world "KWANGYA" is unique in K-pop. #aespa', 'K-pop Facts', 'fact_card', NULL, 'aespa', 'aespa', 'aespa''s lore connects two worlds: real and virtual', 'The "KWANGYA" universe is unlike any other K-pop concept', NULL, false, 'draft', ARRAY['#kpop', '#aespa', '#MY', '#SMCU', '#kpopfact'], 'fact_card', 110);

